🔹 CI/CD Flow with Security Integration

1. Code Commit (Trigger)
  Developer pushes code to GitHub (main/dev branch)
  Workflow is triggered automatically

2. Continuous Integration (CI)
    Goal: Build + Test + Scan code
    ✔ Steps:
        Checkout code
        Install dependencies
        Run unit tests
        Build application
      SAST (Static Code Analysis) → Find vulnerabilities in code
          Example tools:
              CodeQL
              SonarQube

3. Dependency Security
      ✔ Scan third-party libraries for vulnerabilities
          🔐Tools:
              Dependabot
              Snyk

4. Container Security (if using Docker)
      ✔ Scan Docker images before deployment
          🔐Tools:
                Trivy
                Aqua Security

5. Secrets Management
      ✔ Avoid hardcoding secrets
            Use: 
              GitHub Secrets (encrypted)
              Environment variables

6. Continuous Deployment (CD)
      ✔ Deploy application automatically
          Examples:
              Deploy to AWS / Azure / Kubernetes
              Use approval gates for production

7. DAST (Runtime Security Testing)
      ✔ Test running application for vulnerabilities
            🔐 Tools:
                OWASP ZAP
